14/01/2004
LISBON, Portugal -- Wrapping up an official visit to Portugal on Tuesday (13 January), Macedonian President Boris Trajkovski said his country would formally launch its EU membership bid at the end of February.
He noted that an extensive political debate in December had demonstrated the unity of all parties on this issue.
In other news Tuesday, Local Self-Government Minister Aleksander Gestakovski announced that the cabinet would revise the draft administrative division bill, aimed at reducing the number of municipalities from the current 123 to 71.
In separate referendums, a number of municipalities had rejected the new division.
(Utrinski Vesnik - 14/01/04;
AFP, MIA - 13/01/04)
